<exercise>
  <title>C4 - Homogeneous second-order linear IVP (ver. 27)</title>
  <statement>
    <p>Find the solution to the given IVP.</p>
    <me>y''+4y'-5y = 0 \hspace{1em} y(0) = -4 , y'(0) = -10</me>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>y= e^{\left(-5 \, t\right)} - 5 \, e^{t}</me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
